KwaZulu-Natal wants to sell its other tourist attractions too. DURBAN - Thousands of South African and international tourists flock to Durban every festive season, and this year is no different. But KwaZulu-Natal wants to sell its other tourist attractions too. Durban is known for beautiful beaches, warm weather and a place to be. READ:Â Durban increases policing ahead of New Year's Eve celebrations With the city's popularity sealed, provincial authorities are encouraging tourists to explore other parts of the province as well. "Tourism is not only about Durban. We've got a number of tourist attraction points," said KZN premier Sihle Zikalala. Consolidated figures of cash injection into the local economy will be released later.
For now, people continue to enjoy what is left of their holiday.